There are some 120 species of duck, representing a wide variety of shapes, sizes and behaviors.
Some are noisy and gregarious, others shy and elusive. They are familiar animals we think we know.
But most of us don't really know these phenomenal, sophisticated creatures at all.
This program follows a wood duck family as a male and female create a bond, migrate together across thousands of miles,
nurture and protect a brood of chicks, then come full circle as they head to their wintering grounds.
